    <instructions>1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. In a small bowl, mix the macadamia, coconut and cilantro. 
2. Place chicken in a baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper. 
3. Spread each chicken thigh with I teaspoon of mayonnaise.
4. Spread macadamia coconut mixture on each chicken thigh, dividing evenly. 
5. Bake chicken for 45 minutes on center rack, so as not to burn the macadamia nuts. 
8. Serve with fresh lime zest and juice.</instructions>
